President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Indiana and ordered federal assistance to aid recovery efforts in areas affected by severe storms and flooding from February 14 to March 4, 2018. Federal funding will be made available to individuals in several counties for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans. State and local governments, as well as certain nonprofit organizations, can also receive federal funding for emergency work and facility repairs. Hazard mitigation measures will also be eligible for federal funding. David G. Samaniego has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Residents and business owners in the affected counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. For further information, contact the FEMA News Desk.